The paper proposes a novel approach to person re-identification using deep learning and joint representation learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.MM) and learning-to-rank algorithms (cs.AI), which further supports these sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on datasets (VIPeR, CUHK-01, and CAVIAR4REID) commonly used in the person re-identification literature, indicating that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
